  "hook_reason": "I architected a COBOL/mainframe test-automation harness that cut evidence effort by ≈92% and built an LLM-powered analytics dashboard, directly reflecting the automation design and AI-first product ownership this role calls for.",
  "body": "You are looking for someone to execute the roadmap by translating business objectives into technical requirements and designing advanced automations that drive speed and efficiency. As a Senior Delivery Lead / Technical Product Owner at ANZ, I owned the product backlog for major platform modernisations and facilitated workshops with 40+ GMs and executives, improving decision-making efficiency by >55%. At the Australian Taxation Office, I architected a test-automation harness covering 200+ SIT/E2E scenarios that reduced evidence effort from ~3 hours to ~15 minutes per scenario (≈92% reduction). I have also built micro-apps including a Next.js + Supabase analytics application that generates LLM-powered retrospective insights and an end-to-end Langfuse + Phoenix evaluation stack that reduced simulated error-budget breaches by 38%—demonstrating the portfolio of AI-first principles you seek. Additionally, I convened a cross-discipline technical war room that produced a binding automation recommendation in under three hours, reflecting my ability to partner across functions.\n\nI would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my experience building AI-first tooling and orchestrating cross-functional delivery can support your revenue technology team’s biggest projects. I am available for a conversation at your convenience."
}
